title: Specimen of 50-tonne whale is hauled onto a huge truck by a crane as it's being transported to a museum in China
text: show ad That's a jaw-dropping delivery! Specimen of 50-tonne whale is hauled onto a huge truck by a crane as it's being transported to a museum in China Images show a specimen of a sperm whale arriving in Yangkou Port in east China on February 14 The whale died alongside another after they became stranded on a beach in Yangkou, Rudong County A year later and the first whale has been preserved by Xiamen University and returned to Yangkou A museum has been set up to display the whale along with the other when it is fully preserved Published: 14:03 GMT, 15 February 2017 | Updated: 14:33 GMT, 15 February 2017 170 shares
